preamble: Default implementation of HETEROGENEOUS_VALUE, to use when the type of the value in a heterogeneous map does not depend on the type of the key, only on the type of the map.
content:
type ('a, 'map) t = 'map

The type of values. A 'map map maps 'key key to ('key, 'map) value. Can be mutable if desired, unless it is being used in Hash-consed maps and sets.
